{"body": "The seems good in principle. Some comments:\r\n\r\n* Needs documentation\r\n* I'm not keen on the `Record.from(:a => sub_query)` API. Would prefer `Record.from(sub_query, :a)` so the optional second parameter is an alias.\r\n* I don't think the `build_from` stuff should be done when `#from` is called - it should happen when we build the arel.\r\n* Needs a rebase", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5530198", "created_at": "2012-05-05T20:23:48Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6058#issuecomment-5530198", "updated_at": "2012-05-05T20:23:48Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6058, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jonleighton", "type": "User", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523e8b7dbd354364b9010bb0"}, "id": 5530198, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6058"}
